properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County San Gabriel Valley; Catalina and Santa Barbara Islands; Los Angeles County Coast including Downtown Los Angeles
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 1 at 9:42PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...San Gabriel Valley, Los Angeles County Coast including
Downtown Los Angeles, and Catalina and Santa Barbara Islands.

* WHEN...From 8 PM Sunday to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Trees and powerlines could be blown down and a few power
outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds Sunday night across
western portions of Catalina Island, the western portions of
the LA coast, including Malibu to Hollywood Hills, and
foothills of the San Gabriel Valley.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
